Description: The Flight into Egypt: a night piece; the Virgin seated on a donkey holding the Christ Child, while St Joseph leads the way towards the left while holding a lantern; fifth state with shading added overall, for instance between the donkey's ears, on Joseph's right shoulder, in the sky, lower left corner, in the highlight below the lantern, in the Virgin's headdress and robe, before additional cross hatching over nose of donkey, Joseph's right hand, sleeve and chest. 1651 Etching, burin and drypoint Watermark: Strasbourg lily with initials LC´ (Hinterding catalogue, variant A.a.b., datable c.1652)
Curator's comments: For comment and an impression of first state see also F,4.103.
